ICYDK, exercise is just one HALF of a proper training regimen. The other half is #RECOVERY. Without proper recovery, all that hard work training just gets wasted as your muscles and cells aren’t able to rebuild and lock in the gains from exercising. 

Here’s a quick primer on how we like to #recover after a long run:
Compression 🔁: help increase circulation and reduce muscle fatigue
Whole body Cryo ❄️: reduce soreness and inflammation all over
Spot Cryo ❄️: all-natural pain relief for specific joints and muscles 
Oxygen therapy 🌬: breathe in hyper-oxygenated air, giving your cells the metabolic fuel they crave after a hard workout 
Float therapy 🛏: advanced sensory deprivation bed that induces a short bout of deep sleep and recovery 

Come visit #degreetownctr or #degreejaxbeach and let our highly skilled team help YOU develop an amazing recovery program to complement YOUR unique training regimen.

node.text:
09.11.2001
I worked in World Trade Center [WTC4] (New York Board of Trade; Commodities) and was there the morning of September 11th, I remember that day with extreme detail... I remember feeling the building shaking and the windows waving, I remember walking down the emergency stairwell, I remember exiting the building and dodging lifeless bodies bouncing off the floor, I remember making eye contact with a dead person, and I remember seeing the North Tower [WTC1] burning with a large hole going through it. I also remember looking up and seeing the second plane fly into the South Tower [WTC2], people jumping out of windows knowing their fate. I remember running down the street a while later because the building started to collapse, and I remember being covered in that dust thinking it’s particles from humans. I also remember not having phone service and finally getting home after walking 20 miles from Manhattan to Queens to see my worried family and friends — I remember the look in my mom’s eyes when she saw I was still alive.

I remember with great detail, every feeling and emotion from that day. I remember smells, images, the energy, conversations with strangers and the blisters on my feet from walking in new dress shoes.

I also remember my friends and acquaintances that weren’t lucky enough to make it out alive — and some never found. I remember the funerals I went to and I remember the families it effected... and still effects.

It wasn’t until 3 years ago (2017) that I revisited Ground Zero, I had vivid flashbacks like a War Veteran having PTSD. I completely broke down and fell apart sobbing in my girlfriend’s (now wife’s) arms. I didn’t realize how much I buried and avoided those emotions until that moment.

Life is short and extremely unpredictable. Tell the people you care about you love them. Live life to the fullest. Forgive people and yourself. Stand up for people that can’t/won’t stand up for themselves. Don’t let your heart be filled with hatred. Take chances. Apologize. It’s ok to cry. Show compassion and empathy. Be kind to yourself and most importantly to me, take the “LONG JOURNEY HOME”!

*** These are photos of the building I worked in (WTC4)

We love plants here at Boxx HQ, who doesn’t, but did you know what benefits they can bring to your office? 🌱 Plants have been shown to boost employee productivity 12%
🌱 They add clean air, removing toxins and adding fresh air to your space 🌱Live planting regulates indoor temperatures 🌱 Plants reduce ambient noise by around 5 decibels
🌱 Plants have been shown to improve well-being and reduce sick days.

Here’s our little #kokedama hanging in the corner of the studio doing its thing. Thanks @hillcrossfurniture and @carlhansenandson for hosting us in #Clerkenwell and to @plantdesignsldn for guidance in our Kokedama’s conception!

node.text:
Phalaenopsis

Es uno de los géneros más cultivados a nivel mundial y proveniente de Asia.

Es una orquídea que se recomienda tenerla en lugares donde la luz solar no le dé directamente. Se puede considerar una planta de interior. Debe irrigarse una vez por semana y fertilizarse cada 15 días con un abono foliar que puede ser de mantenimiento o floración y cada 4 ó 5 meses con un abono granulado de liberación lenta.

Hay una diversidad de colores y tamaños de la flor de esta planta. En Taiwán, China y Costa Rica existen biofábricas que se encargan de la reproducción de esta popular especie.

En la República Dominicana hay varios viveros que se encargan de su producción, específicamente en la zona de Jarabacoa y Constanza.

Su mayor floración es desde noviembre hasta marzo, debido a que en esta época la temperatura tiene a disminuir. .

"Flamboyanes del Botánico" 
Delonix regia. Árbol originario de Madagascar, cultivado en todos los trópicos del mundo por la belleza de sus flores. El nombre "Flamboyant" viene de la palabra Flamme (francés) que significa flamear, ya que en algunos lugares se le llama "árbol de llama o de fuego", por su color rojo-naranja encendido. Es una especie caducifolia (que en determinada época del año pierden sus hojas), quedando solo con los frutos (Vainas). .

Las palmas son plantas de gran utilidad para la humanidad. Después de las gramíneas y las leguminosas, es la familia de plantas más útil al hombre. Además de su uso ornamental, son aprovechadas como alimento, bebidas, medicina, aceites, biocombustible, ceremoniales, fibras, utensilios domésticos, ceras, materia prima para construcciones, y artesanías.
